text: National Highway 143AG, commonly referred to as NH 143AG is a national highway in India. It is a secondary route of National Highway 43. NH-143AG runs in the state of Jharkhand in India. == Route == NH143AG connects Lohardaga, Bhandra, Bero, Karra, Khunti and Tamar in the state of Jharkhand. == Junctions == : Terminal near Lohardaga. : Terminal near Tamar. == See also == * List of National Highways in India * List of National Highways in India by state == References == == External links == * NH 143AG on OpenStreetMap Category:National highways in India Category:National Highways in Jharkhand
